# Kahoot Quiz — One‑Pager

## What This Is (short)

A quick, inclusive **holiday‑themed Kahoot** your whole TD team can play together (in‑person or remote). Players join from phones/laptops at **kahoot.it**, enter the game PIN, and answer fun, general winter/Christmas questions. Perfect for a light 20–25 minute segment at the party.

## How to Play (announce)

1. “Open **kahoot.it** (or the Kahoot app). Enter the **Game PIN** and a nickname.”
2. “Points = **accuracy + speed**. Streaks boost your score.”
3. “Pick a fun, work‑appropriate nickname—we’ll award a small prize for the coolest nickname at the end.”
4. “We have **12–15 questions**. Top 3 win bragging rights (or prizes if provided).”

---

## General, Christmas‑Themed Sample Questions (inclusive)

> Copy‑paste any 12–15 of these into your Kahoot. Keep answers brief and neutral.

1. **Which song includes the lyric “fa‑la‑la‑la‑la”?**
   A) Jingle Bells
   B) Deck the Halls
   C) Silent Night
   D) Joy to the World
   **Answer:** B

2. **What date is Boxing Day in many countries?**
   A) Dec 24
   B) Dec 25
   C) Dec 26
   D) Jan 1
   **Answer:** C

3. **Which of these is NOT a reindeer name?**
   A) Comet
   B) Blitzen
   C) Dasher
   D) Thunder
   **Answer:** D

4. **Classic winter drink often served warm:**
   A) Lemonade
   B) Hot chocolate
   C) Iced tea
   D) Espresso tonic
   **Answer:** B

5. **Common decoration made from evergreen branches:**
   A) Wreath
   B) Bunting
   C) Lantern
   D) Banner
   **Answer:** A

6. **In ‘Home Alone’, Kevin is left behind in which city?**
   A) New York
   B) Chicago
   C) Boston
   D) Toronto
   **Answer:** B

7. **Traditional red‑and‑white holiday plant:**
   A) Poinsettia
   B) Orchid
   C) Sunflower
   D) Peony
   **Answer:** A

8. **What do many people build after a snowfall?**
   A) Sandcastle
   B) Snowman
   C) Leaf pile
   D) Birdhouse
   **Answer:** B

9. **Which phrase means exchanging gifts anonymously at work?**
   A) Secret Santa
   B) Mystery Elf
   C) Hidden Helper
   D) Snowy Swap
   **Answer:** A

10. **Which dessert is often shaped like a log?**
    A) Fruit tart
    B) Yule log cake
    C) Apple pie
    D) Cheesecake
    **Answer:** B

11. **Common cookie shape for the season:**
    A) Star
    B) Triangle
    C) Octagon
    D) Crescent wrench
    **Answer:** A

12. **Popular holiday comedy starring Will Ferrell:**
    A) The Holiday
    B) Elf
    C) Jingle All the Way
    D) The Santa Clause
    **Answer:** B

13. **Which item is often hung by a fireplace?**
    A) Scarf
    B) Stocking
    C) Umbrella
    D) Skates
    **Answer:** B

14. **What’s a common outdoor winter activity?**
    A) Kayaking
    B) Gardening
    C) Ice skating
    D) Surfing
    **Answer:** C

15. **Which spice is common in seasonal drinks and baking?**
    A) Turmeric
    B) Cinnamon
    C) Dill
    D) Cumin
    **Answer:** B

16. **Which color combo is often associated with the season?**
    A) Purple & Gold
    B) Red & Green
    C) Teal & Orange
    D) Black & White
    **Answer:** B

17. **What might you find at a winter market?**
    A) Sunblock stations
    B) Ice sculptures
    C) Beach volleyball
    D) Fireworks every hour
    **Answer:** B

18. **Which phrase is often used in greeting cards?**
    A) Have a cool summer!
    B) Happy Holidays!
    C) See you next fall!
    D) Good luck on exams!
    **Answer:** B

---

